getJarEntryPart

public java.lang.String getJarEntryPart()
Returns the (percent-encoded) part of the jar uri regarding the jar entry, the part after the '!' symbol.

Example: 

 /myjarfolder/my%20doc.xslt

Returns:
a string, never null.

getJarURI

public java.lang.String getJarURI()
Returns the (percent-encoded) part of the jar uri regarding the jar file, without the entry.

Returns the part after the jar: scheme and before the '!' symbol. prefix.

Example: 

 file:/f:/my%20folder/myjar.jar

Returns:
a string, never null.
